<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>HelloTrello</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="tint">
    <header>
      <h1>HelloTrello!</h1>
      <p>
        This site is populated with content from a public <a href="https://trello.com/b/Zzc0USwZ/hellotrello">Trello board</a>. Every deployment pulls the latest content from the Trello API and populates this site at build time on <a href="https://netlify.com">Netlify</a>.
      </p>
    </header>
  </div>
  <main>
    {% for card in cards %}
    <section>
      <h2>{{ card.name }}</h2>
      <div>
      {% markdown %}
        {{- card.desc }}
      {% endmarkdown %}
      </div>
    </section>
    {% endfor %}
  </main>
  <div class="tint">
    <footer>
      <p>
        The Trello board which is the source od this content has columns for staged and for live content. These power different branch builds, but the code on <a href="https://stage--hellotrello.netlify.app">staging</a> and <a href="https://hellotrello.netlify.app">live</a> are identical.
      </p>
      <p>
        Check out the <a href="{{ pkg.repository.url }}">code in GitHub</a> to learn more and try this out for yourself.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
